# Global Rules

## Global Coding Rules

### Global Typescript Coding Standards

- Use TypeScript for all new frontend code
- Prefer types to interfaces
- Follow SOLID and Clean Code principles
- Prefer async/await over callbacks
- Write comprehensive error handling
- Include JSDoc comments for functions
- Use meaningful variable names

### Global Python Coding Standards

- Use Python for all new backend code
- Follow SOLID and Clean Code principles
- Prefer async/await over callbacks
- Write comprehensive error handling
- Include docstrings comments for functions
- Use meaningful variable names

### Global Code Style Rules

- Use 2 spaces for indentation except in Python
- Use 4 spaces for indentation in Python
- No trailing whitespace
- Semicolons should be avoided
- Use single quotes for strings
- Maximum line length: 88 characters

### Global Testing Guidelines

- Write tests for all public functions
- Use Vitest for unit tests
- Implement E2E tests with Playwright
- Maintain 60% code coverage
- Use descriptive test names

## Project Specific Rules

### Technology Stack

- React 19 with TypeScript
- React Router v7
- SQLite database
- Tailwind CSS for styling

### Coding Guidelines

- Use functional components with hooks
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Follow atomic design principles
- Use React Query for data fetching
- Maintain 60% test coverage

## React TypeScript Rules

### Component Standards

- Use functional components exclusively
- Implement proper prop types with types
- Follow naming convention: PascalCase for components and camelCase for functions
- Use custom hooks for complex logic
- Implement proper error handling

### State Management

- Use React Query for server state
- Use Zustand for client state
- Avoid prop drilling beyond 2 levels
- Implement optimistic updates where appropriate

## Backend API Guidelines

### Architecture

- Follow RESTful conventions
- Use middleware for authentication
- Implement proper logging
- Use environment variables for configuration

### Error Handling

- Return consistent error responses
- Log all errors with context
- Use appropriate HTTP status codes
- Implement request validation

## Database Guidelines

### Query Optimization

- Use indexes for frequently queried fields
- Avoid N+1 queries
- Implement proper pagination
- Use connection pooling

### Security

- Sanitize all inputs
- Use parameterized queries
- Implement proper access controls
- Regular security audits
